Lufs version 0.12
=================

This is perlufs, a perl plug for lufs.
It allows you to write filesystem implementations in perl.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   # the perl module:
   perl Makefile.PL 
   make
   make test
   make install

   # the C library: 
   cd perlfs
   make
   make install

   # the lufs patch:
   cd lufs-0.9.7
   patch -p1 < lufs-0.97-dlopen-patch.diff
   make
   make install

USAGE

For usage information, consult the Lufs(3pm) manpage.
For programming examples, see the Lufs::Stub(3pm) manpage.

DEPENDENCIES

Of course you need lufs (http://lufs.sf.net) to use this.
At the moment there are no other dependencies, besides a recent perl.

